  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Costoclavicular approach has lots of advantages compared to the lateral sagittal approach for
      infraclavicular brachial plexus block. Although the efficacy of this block has been
      demonstrated in adults, there are no randomized controlled trials in the literature on the
      application of pediatric patients. Our aim was to compare the ultrasound-guided
      infraclavicular and costoclavicular approach in pediatric patients.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
